HEADWORD: Bey
<hw>Bey</hw> <pr>(b⟦amac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Beg</er> a
bey.]</ety> <def>A governor of a province or district in the Turkish
dominions; also, in some places, a prince or nobleman; a beg; <as>as,
the <ex>bey</ex> of Tunis</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

